## 6. DATA MODEL\
\
### 6.1 Default Data (Factory Function)\
\
The `getDefaultData()` function returns a new deep copy of the default ontology each time it is called, preventing object reference pollution.\
\
**Structure:**\
\
```\
\{\
  workflows: [\
    \{ id, name, type, description, owner, frequency, linkedSystems: [] \},\
    ...\
  ],\
  systems: [\
    \{ id, name, category, description, linkedWorkflows: [], linkedUsers: [] \},\
    ...\
  ],\
  personas: [\
    \{ id, name, state, description \},\
    ...\
  ]\
\}\
```\
\
**Default Workflows (5):** Management Escalations (Ad-hoc, Critical), Admin Deadlines (Weekly, Routine), System Maintenance (Monthly), Cross-Team Sync (Weekly), Strategic Planning (Quarterly).\
\
**Default Systems (5):** Shared Sites/SharePoint (Storage), Comm Hub/Slack/Teams (Comms), AI Context Engine (Intelligence), Project Tracker/Jira (Tracking), Exec Dashboard (Reporting).\
\
**Default Personas (4):** Reactive Firefighter, Deep Focus Architect, Process Admin, Bridge Builder.\
\
**Total default nodes:** 14\
\
### 6.2 Context Map (Relationship Adjacency)\
\
A JavaScript object (`contextMap` or similar) that defines the edges of the knowledge graph \'97 which workflows connect to which systems, and which personas are associated with which workflows/systems. This is used by `handleItemClick()` to determine highlighting behavior and by the Friction Heatmap to calculate compatibility scores.\
\
### 6.3 Persistence Layer\
\
All data is serialized to `localStorage` under a specific key. On page load, the app checks for existing `localStorage` data; if found, it hydrates `ontologyData` from storage instead of calling `getDefaultData()`. Every add-node operation triggers a save to `localStorage`.\
\
