## 7. KEY INTERACTIONS & STATE MANAGEMENT\
\
### 7.1 Simulation Mode Toggle\
- Global state variable tracks current mode (triage / deep_focus / firefighting).\
- On mode change: iterate through all Ontology Explorer node elements and apply/remove CSS classes based on mode-specific rules.\
- Mode rules are defined in a lookup table mapping each mode to arrays of "dimmed" nodes and "highlighted" nodes.\
\
### 7.2 Node Click \uc0\u8594  Insight Generation\
- Click a node \uc0\u8594  `handleItemClick(nodeId, nodeType)`.\
- Lookup relationships in `contextMap`.\
- Highlight connected nodes in other columns (add `.active-context` class).\
- Show insight box with connection summary.\
- Display "Analyze with Gemini \uc0\u10024 " button.\
- On AI button click: construct prompt with node context, call Gemini API, parse response with `marked.js`, render in insight box.\
\
### 7.3 Heatmap Cell Click \uc0\u8594  Friction Resolution\
- Click a red/orange cell \uc0\u8594  extract workflow name (column) and system name (row).\
- Call Gemini with a structured prompt asking for the friction source and a context engineering fix.\
- Render formatted response in a modal or inline container.\
\
### 7.4 Add Node Flow\
- User fills form in Input Studio.\
- On submit: validate inputs, create node object, push to appropriate `ontologyData` array, update `localStorage`, re-render Ontology Explorer columns and Heatmap, show success feedback.\
- If "Auto-Connect \uc0\u10024 " is used: call Gemini to predict relationships, auto-check the relevant linking checkboxes.\
\
### 7.5 Reset Flow (Soft Reset)\
- Clear `localStorage`.\
- Set `ontologyData = getDefaultData()`.\
- Hide all AI result containers, insight boxes, scenario outputs.\
- Reset simulation mode to default (Morning Triage).\
- Re-render columns via `renderColumns()`.\
- Re-render heatmap via `renderHeatmap()`.\
- Charts are static \'97 no re-render needed.\
\
