## 9. AI INTEGRATION DETAILS\
\
The app includes at least five distinct Gemini API call patterns:\
\
1. **Node Analyzer** (`triggerAIAnalysis`) \'97 Sends selected node + its connections. Prompt asks Gemini to act as the "Ontology Engine" and explain optimization opportunities.\
\
2. **Roadmap Action Planner** (`triggerRoadmapAI`) \'97 Sends a roadmap step description. Prompt asks for a concrete 3-step implementation checklist.\
\
3. **Prompt Artifact Generator** (`triggerAIPromptGen`) \'97 Sends a selected triad combination. Prompt asks Gemini to write the actual `system_instruction` JSON for configuring an LLM agent.\
\
4. **Smart Friction Resolver** (`analyzeFriction`) \'97 Sends a workflow/system pair. Prompt asks Gemini to explain the friction source and propose a context engineering fix.\
\
5. **Context Scenario Simulator** (`generateScenario`) \'97 Sends current mode and active nodes. Prompt asks for a vivid narrative description of the user experience.\
\
All responses are processed through `marked.parse()` before being inserted into the DOM, ensuring proper rendering of Markdown formatting.\
\
The API key is expected to be present as a runtime-injected variable (e.g., `const apiKey = ""` which is populated by the hosting environment). Hardcoded validation checks against the API key are avoided because the Gemini Canvas environment injects the key transparently.\
\
